---
import ProfilePill from './profile-pill.astro'
---
<section aria-labelledby="how-it-works-heading" class="mx-auto max-w-[680px] px-4 pt-12 pb-4 sm:px-14">
  <h2 id="how-it-works-heading" class="m-0 mb-[18px] text-[22px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.014em]">How it works</h2>
  <p class="m-0 mb-4 text-[15.5px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-soft">
    You create a profile in claude-profiles for each Claude account — give it a name like
    <ProfilePill name="Personal" color="var(--color-profile-orange)" />,
    <ProfilePill name="Work" color="var(--color-profile-steel)" />, or
    <ProfilePill name="Acme Co." color="var(--color-profile-sage)" />
    — and pick a colour. The app generates a Mac launcher
    (<code class="rounded bg-cream-2 px-1.5 py-px font-mono text-[0.88em]">Claude (Personal).app</code>)
    and a CLI command
    (<code class="rounded bg-cream-2 px-1.5 py-px font-mono text-[0.88em]">claude-personal</code>),
    both named after the profile.
  </p>
  <p class="m-0 text-[15.5px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-soft">
    Open them from Spotlight, the Dock, or your terminal. They never share state — each one keeps its own login, history, and settings. Delete a profile and both artifacts go away.
  </p>
</section>
